Looking at the solution, the only non-local dependencies are the `@true_values` / `@false_values` module attributes used inside the `:boolean` clause. That's the sole thing in the fill-in that can break compilation of module `CsvLoader` (e.g. an attribute-resolution / `in`-with-attribute issue at the insertion point). Making the `:boolean` clause self-contained by inlining the literals removes that dependency while preserving the exact semantics described in the prompt.

